3. BoxCox transformation

lambda <- BoxCox.lambda(ts)
train_split %>% BoxCox(lambda = lambda) %>% tsdisplay()

train1<-diff(diff(train_split,lag = 12))
tsdisplay(train1)

4.ets model in 2000-2015 period to check which ets model should be used.

Modelets<-ets(train_split)
Modelets

## Model df: 14.   Total lags used: 24
forecastets<-forecast(Modelets,h=36)
autoplot(forecastets,ylab="Global Temperature")+autolayer(test_split,series = "Actual")

9.2 ARIMA models

k <- 156
n <- length(ts19new)
p <- 12
H <- 36
st <- tsp(ts19new)[1]+(k-2)/p

9.21 Arima(0,0,1)(0,1,1)

mae_1 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)
mae_2 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)


rmse_1 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)
rmse_2 <- matrix(NA,n-k-35,H)


aicc_1 <- array(NA)
aicc_2 <- array(NA)


for(i in 1:(n-k-35))
{
  ## One Month rolling forecasting
  # Expanding Window 
  train_1 <- window(ts19new, end=st + i/p)  ## Window Length: k+i
  
  # Sliding Window - keep the training window of fixed length. 
  # The training set always consists of k observations.
  train_2 <- window(ts19new, start=st+(i-k+1)/p, end=st+i/p) ## Window Length: k
  
  test <- window(ts19new, start=st + (i+1)/p, end=st + (i+H)/p) ## Window Length: H

  if (i<4) {
  cat(c("*** CV", i,":","len(Expanding Window):",length(train_1), "len(Sliding Window):",length(train_2), "len(Test):",length(test),'\n'  ))
  cat(c("*** TRAIN -  Expanding WIndow:",tsp(train_1)[1],'-',tsp(train_1)[2],'\n'))
  cat(c("*** TRAIN - Sliding WIndow:",tsp(train_2)[1],'-',tsp(train_2)[2],'\n'))
  cat(c("*** TEST:",tsp(test)[1],'-',tsp(test)[2],'\n'))
  cat("*************************** \n \n")
  }
  
  fit_1 <- Arima(train_1, order=c(0,0,1), 
                 seasonal=list(order=c(0,1,1), period=p),
                 lambda = lambda19, method="ML")
  fcast_1 <- forecast(fit_1, h=H)
  
  fit_2 <- Arima(train_2, order=c(0,0,1), 
                 seasonal=list(order=c(0,1,1), period=p),
                 lambda = lambda19, method="ML")
  fcast_2 <- forecast(fit_2, h=H)
  
  
  
  mae_1[i,1:length(test)] <- abs(fcast_1[['mean']]-test)
  mae_2[i,1:length(test)] <- abs(fcast_2[['mean']]-test)
  
  mean(sqrt(fcast_1[['mean']]-test)^2)
  
  rmse_1[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_1[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  rmse_2[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_2[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5

  aicc_1[i] <- fcast_1$model$aicc
  aicc_2[i] <- fcast_2$model$aicc
}

  mae_8[i,1:length(test)] <- abs(fcast_8[['mean']]-test)
 
  
  
  rmse_3[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_3[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  rmse_4[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_4[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  rmse_5[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_5[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  rmse_6[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_6[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  rmse_7[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_7[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  rmse_8[i,1:length(test)] <- (mean((fcast_8[['mean']]-test)^2))^0.5
  
  
  aicc_3[i] <- fcast_3$model$aicc
  aicc_4[i] <- fcast_4$model$aicc
  aicc_5[i] <- fcast_5$model$aicc
  aicc_6[i] <- fcast_6$model$aicc
  aicc_7[i] <- fcast_7$model$aicc
